ents of pressure and energy density expressed as\n$\\Gamma_{th}=1+(P_{th}/\\epsilon_{th})$, often used in astrophysical\nsimulations, exhibits a stronger dependence on density than on proton fraction\nand temperature in both MFT and TL calculations. The prominent peak of\n$\\Gamma_{th}$ at supra-nuclear density found in MFT is, however, suppressed in\nTL calculations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Feb 2016 20:23:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-01"}
